    <id>https://www.nber.org/papers/w34623</id>
    <title>Principled Identification of Structural Dynamic Models</title>
    <updated>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Neville Francis, Peter Reinhard Hansen &amp; Chen Tong</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;b&gt; NBER Working Papers&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;We take a new perspective on identification in structural dynamic models: rather than imposing restrictions, we optimize an objective. This provides new theoretical insights into traditional Cholesky identification. A correlation-maximizing objective yields an Order- and Scale-Invariant Identification Scheme (OASIS) that selects the orthogonal rotation that best aligns structural shocks with their reduced-form innovations. We revisit a large number of SVAR studies and find, across 22 published SVARs, that the correlations between structural and reduced-form shocks are generally high.</content>
    <link href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w34623"/>
    <category term="NBER"/>
    <published>2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00</published>
